<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0">
    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>The Secretary of State to the
                            President</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Malta</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d150</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">150</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1944-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1944-12-01T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="150" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d150">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">865.01/12–144</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-01">December 1,
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Special Information for the President</hi>
                </p>
                <p rend="center">[Excerpts]<note n="1" xml:id="d150fn1">For other excerpts from this
                        memorandum, see <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_250">pp.
                            250</ref>, <ref target="#pg_266">266</ref>, <ref target="#pg_430">430</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>These international developments of the past two or three days will be of
                    especial interest to you:</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . . </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="italic">New Polish Cabinet</hi>. Schoenfeld reports that the new
                    Polish Government is generally considered to be made up of the anti-Russian wing
                    of the London Poles. The <persName corresp="#p_NDM1">Chairman</persName> of the
                    Lublin Committee, Osobka-Morawski, in a speech reported by the Soviet press, has
                    indicated the willingness of his organization to cooperate with <persName corresp="#p_MS1">Mikolajczyk</persName> but only on the platform supported
                    by the Lublin Committee.</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . . . . . . . . . </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SERJ1">E. R. <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius,
                            Jr</hi>.</persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
</TEI>
